      "body": "I'm inclined to agree, that such a \"probabilistic decrease\" could be done when really the most recent block was mined \"too long ago\". But it happens regularly even after two minutes. This can't be \"too long ago\" when it is to assume that a new block happens every 10 minutes.\r\n\r\nAlso note: I'm **not** talking about the `progress` from the log file, which seems to sit happily at `1.000000`. I'm talking about the `verification progress` value, output by the command `bitcoin-cli -getinfo`, which starts to decrease after a few minutes to `99.9999%` and below.",
